quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,106,"They will say: "
  23,107,""
  23,108,"He (Allâh) will say: "
  25,52,"So obey not the disbelievers, but strive against them (by preaching) with the utmost endeavour with it (the Qur’ân)."
  25,53,"And it is He Who has let free the two seas (kinds of water): this is palatable and sweet, and that is salt and bitter; and He has set a barrier and a complete partition between them."
  25,54,"And it is He Who has created man from water, and has appointed for him kindred by blood, and kindred by marriage. And your Lord is Ever All-Powerful to do what He wills."
  26,25,"[Fir‘aun (Pharaoh)] said to those around: "
  26,26,"[Mûsâ (Moses)] said: "
  26,27,"[Fir‘aun (Pharaoh)] said: "